00:05:16,572 --> 00:05:22,314
Developers in general contacting me,

104
00:05:22,314 --> 00:05:24,755
submitting decks, submitting pitches.

105
00:05:26,776 --> 00:05:33,262
The first one is definitely the conflation of reach and discoverability.

106
00:05:33,262 --> 00:05:37,967
It's super important and it applies to a lot of us,

107
00:05:37,967 --> 00:05:40,950
whether you've made a game in the past or not.

108
00:05:40,950 --> 00:05:44,473
Reach is just not discoverability,

109
00:05:44,473 --> 00:05:46,315
and I would say it actually applies even more to us

110
00:05:46,315 --> 00:05:50,679
with social media followings and previous project communities.

111
00:05:50,679 --> 00:05:52,060
It's not to say it can't help.

112
00:05:52,730 --> 00:05:57,524
So, like, if you've made a game in the past and you have a huge community, that is obviously

113
00:05:57,524 --> 00:05:58,066
not a downside.

114
00:05:58,066 --> 00:05:58,647
That's a huge help.

115
00:05:59,073 --> 00:06:01,895
but it's not one and the same.

116
00:06:01,895 --> 00:06:04,277
Reach is useful for pushing marketing materials

117
00:06:04,277 --> 00:06:07,258
and hopefully means that you'll have people

118
00:06:07,258 --> 00:06:08,939
who will champion your game,

119
00:06:08,939 --> 00:06:10,640
both on the consumer and the business side

120
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:11,681
because you have a reputation.

